from
plenary sessions, interactive panel discussions and case studies focussing
on: 
- The route towards achieving a fully operational smart grid, including
the introduction of CADs
- Smart grid engagement with the future customer
- The role of utilities in EV uptakeUnderstanding the influence of weather on
energy demand
- The role of innovation in delivering future networks - projects
at SGN�
- DMA for Real: the learning from NINES first winter
- The Milton Keynes FALCON smart grid: integrating demand side response from
industrial and
commercial customers
- The needs and benefits of distributed generation
- Accelerating renewable connections through active network management
Demand response in Europe and the way ahead

This event will be of interest to regulators and policy makers,
DNOs, the supply chain, energy suppliers, aggregators and renewable generators.

I do hope you and your colleagues can join us in March and I would appreciate
you forwarding information to contacts you feel may be interested in
